parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak and Fuel Pump Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel leak and fuel pump module failure can cause fuel vapors to leak into the cabin of the vehicle, creating a fire hazard and potential health risks. The strong fuel odor can also be overwhelming for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Strong fuel smell
fuel vapors leaking into the cabin
fuel leaking from the top of the tank
fuel dripping down the back side of the tank onto the hot exhaust pipes
fuel smell in the garage
fuel smell inside the vehicle
fuel fumes filling the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Valve Guide Failure and Engine Damage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of valve guides can cause valves to drop, leading to engine damage, loss of power steering and brakes, and potentially causing accidents or fires.
symptoms: Loud ticking or knocking noise from the engine
excessive valve train noise
engine failure
loss of power
smoke or oil leaking from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gasoline Odor and Potential Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The strong odor of gasoline can be a potential fire hazard, especially if the vehicle is parked in an enclosed space.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline
especially after filling up the tank
no visible leaks.
